text: Ana Sinatashvili (; born 29 June 1996) is a Georgian footballer who plays as a forward for FC Martve. She has played officially for the senior Georgia women's national team. ==International career== Sinatashvili capped for Georgia at senior level during the UEFA Women's Euro 2017 qualifying Group 6, in a 0–3 home loss to the Czech Republic on 22 September 2015. ==References== Category:1996 births Category:Living people Category:Women's association football forwards Category:Women's footballers from Georgia (country) Category:Georgia (country) women's international footballers Category:FC Martve players
